                            <comment id="14692988" author="tan9" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2015 06:14:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12750036/12750036_landscape-rotated.pdf&quot; title=&quot;landscape-rotated.pdf attached to PDFBOX-2930&quot;&gt;landscape-rotated.pdf&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is a document with 90&#176;/270&#176; rotation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;PDFPageable&lt;/tt&gt; does not handle it well as following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12750037/12750037_prints.jpg&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Debug information on rotated portrait document:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12750034/12750034_debug_info_on_rotated_document.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Debug information on normal document:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12750035/12750035_debug_info_on_not_rotated_document.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe we should rotate the media box as well as crop box to conform to the Java printing&apos;s nature?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
